Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_lib_cell_leakage_power(25.10)            get_lib_cell_leakage_power(25.10)

Name
       get_lib_cell_leakage_power

Syntax
       get_lib_cell_leakage_power

       [-help]

       -cell <string>

       [-file <string>]

       [-stateleakagegrp]

       [ {-view <string> | -delay_corner <string>}

       [-power_domain <string>]]

       [ -early  | -late  ]

       Returns the default leakage power of a cell.

       Parameters

       -help  Prints out the command usage

       -cell <string>
              Specifies  the  cell  Name  for  which  Leakage Power need to be
              fetched (string, required)

       -delay_corner <string>
              Selects cell from specified delay corner

       -early Selects cell from early library of the specified  delay  corner.
              If  this  option  is not specified by default late will be used.
              (bool, optional)

       -file <string>
              Specifies a.Name of the output file. (string, optional)

       -late  Selects cell from late library of the specified delay corner. If
              this option is not specified  by  default  late  will  be  used.
              (bool, optional)

       -power_domain <string>
              Selects  cell  from  the  library  of the specified power domain
              (string, optional)

       -stateleakagegrp
              Reports state dependent leakage power information.

       -view string
              Selects the cell from the specified view.

       Examples

              * The following example reports state independent  cell  leakage
                power along with return value:

                get_lib_cell_leakage_power -cell xyz

              * The following command shows state dependent groups:

                get_lib_cell_leakage_power -cell xyz -stateleakagegrp

